    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-26T18:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-26T18:36:00-05:00" n="1224"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1224">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2906.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-26T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 25, 7 p.m. I learn at the Foreign Office that orders have been sent
                    to the commander of the forces at Ciudad Juárez to <pb facs="0996" n="880"
                        xml:id="pg_880"/> engage the revolutionary forces at a point about 13 miles
                    distant from the city, and under no circumstances to make a resistance in Ciudad
                    Juárez. These instructions have also been communicated to the Mexican consul at
                    El Paso.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
